Fix worker pool socket, spawn, and hung-worker recovery.

The patch keeps cached socket paths authoritative, propagates that path into
-Q workers, rate-limits startup respawns without sliding the grace window,
tracks exact worker process objects owned by the root Emacs, and recovers an
idle connectable worker only after repeated full-probe failures.  Busy workers
are never killed; unowned workers are reported once and left untouched.

